## 🏢 Intended Workflow or Task

Step 1 of the production chain — runs once per background after the artist submits their completed colour key for review

- **Trigger:** Style check completed (P06
- **Actor:** Senior artist / art director
- **Timing:** Before asset documentation and production
- **Next step:** No issues or LOW only → feeds into P08 (Asset Documentation). HIGH or MEDIUM issues → returned to artist for correction.

```
P06 style check returns PASS or CONDITIONAL PASS
      ↓
[P07 RUNS — identifies missing or incomplete details]
      ↓
Supervisor reviews missing detail report
      ↓
HIGH / MEDIUM issues → returned to artist for correction
LOW only or no issues → feeds into P08 asset documentation
```

---

## ❗ Problem Being Solved
Cut down on:

- time-consuming (20–40 minutes per scene) and manually determining shot type, camera angle and compositional approach   
- inconsistent between artists
- heavily dependent on individual experience

**Pain points addressed:**
- incomplete scene specifications
- unclear design instructions
- late discovery of missing elements
- Layout brief requirements not carried through to finished background 

## ⚡ Automation Potential

**Level: Medium-High**

| Dimension | Assessment |
|-----------|------------|
| Repetitiveness | Triggered once per location per episode |
| Data availability | Requires location brief, layout brief, style check and background description as inputs |
| Human judgment needed | High — Supervisor confirms HIGH priority issues and makes return/proceed decision |
| Integration possibility | Output can be attached directly to location entry in Shotgrid or Notion |
| Estimated time saving | ~70% — from 30–45 min to 10 min per background |

**Human-in-the-loop role:** Senior artist validates and decides which gaps require action

---

## ⚠️ Risks and Limitations

| Risk | Level | Mitigation |
|------|-------|------------|
| AI flags details as missing that are present in background but not in written description | **High** | Self-critique step built into prompt instructs model to review its own findings before finalising — reduces false positives |
| misses details that require visual inspection of actual background file | **High** | Supervisor conducts visual review of HIGH priority items against physical file before returning to artist |
| Incomplete briefs passed as inputs produce incomplete missing detail check | Medium | Prompt grounding constraint limits check to briefs provided — incomplete inputs flagged in output |
| Junior artist proceeds without art director review | **High** | Prompt grounding constraint limits check to briefs provided — incomplete inputs flagged in output |

**Overall risk rating: HIGH** — Supervisor visual confirmation of all HIGH priority issues is non-negotiable before background is returned or approved.

